<!DOCTYPE html>
<html ng-app="a2.login">

<head>
    <% include fragments/header %>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>RFCx Arbimon - Connect with RFCx</title>
</head>

<body>
    <% include fragments/home-nav %>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-12">
                <div class="panel panel-default pull-right my-5 ml-5" style="max-width:500px;min-width:320px">
                    <div class="panel-heading">
                        <h3 class="my-2">Status &nbsp;
                        <% if (!user || user.isAnonymousGuest) { %>
                            <span class="label">Unknown</span>
                        <% } else if (user.rfcx_id) { %>
                            <span class="label label-success">Complete</span>
                        <% } else { %>
                            <span class="label label-warning">Not started</span>
                        <% } %>
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                    <% if (!user || user.isAnonymousGuest) { %>
                        <p><a href="/login">Login</a> to check your status.</p>
                    <% } else if (user.rfcx_id) { %>
                        <p>Your account is already connected to RFCx.</p>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <h2 class="panel-title mb-4">Start migration now</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>If you do not have an RFCx account:
                               <p class="my-4"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="<%- auth0UniversalLoginUrl %>&screen_hint=signup">Create an RFCx account</a></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>If you have an RFCx account:
                                <p class="my-4"><a class="btn btn-default" href="<%- auth0UniversalLoginUrl %>">Connect with RFCx account</a></p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    <% } %>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h1>Arbimon II account migration</h1>
                
                <p style="font-size:large">As an Arbimon user, you are now part of a comprehensive technology ecosystem to support bioacoustics research! Our goal
                is to make Arbimon the best platform for your research, conservation, and management projects. With one single login,
                you will now have access to the following applications:</p>

                <ul style="font-size:large">
                    <li class="mb-4"><strong>Companion</strong> - used in conjunction with your AudioMoth devices to mark deployment location (with photos), manage large
                numbers of devices, and streamline ingestion into Arbimon for analysis.</li>
                    <li class="mb-4"><strong>Ingest</strong> - upload large volumes of audio as a background process while you continue to work in Arbimon.</li>
                    <li class="mb-4"><strong>Edge</strong> (coming soon!) - upgraded version of AudioMoth with exceptional battery life thatâ€™s solar powered, allowing you to
                leave it in the field for long periods of time before retrieving it.</li>
                    <li class="mb-4"><strong>Explorer</strong> (coming soon!) - engage your audio in a captivating, colorful spectrogram format and share snippets with other
                colleagues in the community.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="mb-4">Migrating your current Arbimon account is simple! Follow these steps:</h3>

                <ol style="font-size:large">
                    <li class="mb-4">Ensure you are logged in with your existing Arbimon II username and password.
                        <div class="mt-2"><img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step1.png"></div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-4">Click the link at the top to start migration.
                        <div class="mt-2"><img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step2.png"></div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-4">On the right hand side, select one of the options to start migrating.
                        <div class="mt-2"><img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step3a.png">
                        <img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step3b.png">
                        <img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step3c.png"></div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-4">If you created a new RFCx account then <strong>check your email and click on the link in the verification email</strong>.
                        <div class="mt-2"><img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step4a.png">
                        <img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step4b.png"></div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-4">After verification is complete, continue the login.
                        <div class="mt-2"><img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step5.png"></div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-4">You should be redirected back to this page and the status will be complete.
                        <div class="mt-2"><img class="outlined" style="max-width:300px" src="/images/docs/connect-with-rfcx-step6.png"></div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <% include fragments/footer %>
</body>

</html>
